A statement issued by the Department of Trade and Industry (DTI) said that African Bespoke Apparel (ABA) operates within the textile, clothing and footwear sector and had created about 450 job opportunities within the first four months of operation. ABA was approved a funding grant of R35.5 million by DTI’s Black Industrial Scheme (BIS). The project is co-funded by the KwaZulu-Natal government’s growth fund. 